
Col&lt;U+00E9&gt;gio Santa Maria is a Catholic secondary school founded in S&lt;U+00E3&gt;o Paulo, Brazil by the Sisters of the Holy Cross in 1947. It is considered one of the best Paulist schools by Veja magazine.
In the past, it was a girls-only school.




